title: 820-3662 no vCore
message:
Board was dead when it came in. Had 12.6V on PPBUS. only corrosion near U7200 and the wifi plug J3501. Replaced U7200 and got fan spin. Discovered I was missing PP1V05 and was able to resore that by replacing U7600. 

I have ALL_SYS_PWRGD but no VCore. Is there a way to tell if the SMC is the issue or FDMF? I dont have a good board to compare to.

title: 820-3662 no vCore
message: Dah. Nevermind. I have a dead short on VCORE. Wasted parts and time trying to fix. 0.1 ohms to ground.
